# Testing Rules

## Jest Unit Tests
- Location: `tests/unit/*.test.ts` or `src/__tests__/*.test.ts`
- Config: `jest` key in `package.json`; uses `ts-jest` preset
- Run: `npm test` or `npm run test:watch`
- Coverage: `npm run test:coverage` (40% line threshold)
- **Never** import ESM-only packages (e.g. `nanoid`) directly — mock or replace with inline helpers
- Mock the `db` singleton with `jest.mock('@/lib/db')` to avoid real DB calls
- Mock Redis with `jest.mock('@/lib/redis')`

## Playwright E2E Tests
- Location: `e2e/*.spec.ts` and `e2e/api/*.spec.ts`
- Config: `playwright.config.ts` at project root
- Auth state saved to `e2e/.auth/user.json` (git-ignored) by `global.setup.ts`
- Run all: `npm run test:e2e`
- Run with UI: `npm run test:e2e:ui`
- Run only API smoke tests: `npx playwright test --project=api`
- **Browsers**: Chromium (primary), Mobile Safari; installed via `playwright-core install`
- Use `page.route()` to mock API responses in browser tests
- API tests use `request` fixture — no browser launched
